						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">NOOPr wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why don't we still have an aftermarket MMC5 board?<br />Is the repro market primarily targeted by suppliers (leaving homebrew second)?</div><br />A pretty simple answer is just that it took <em>many</em> years to get to what we have now. MMC5 is a harder problem still, and will take longer.<br /><br />The idea of an MMC5 mapper is easy to have. It's obvious, and it's just as obvious that it <em>could</em> be done. ...but actually doing it requires one or several people dedicating a portion of their life, and taking some amount of financial risk in it. That part ain't trivial.</div>

